webLinks.linkText: Wallaga Lake Bridge essential maintenance work

properties.otherAdvice:
WALLAGA LAKE BRIDGE ESSENTIAL MAINTENANCE WORK

The bridge will remain open to traffic as early work begins, including setting up the site compound and receiving deliveries.

Motorists may experience a 5 minute delay at times.

The first full closure of the bridge will commence on 29 April 2024.

Standard construction hours are:

Weekdays - 7am to 6pm

Saturdays - 8am to 5pm

Sundays - 8am to 1pm

KEY DATES

Monday 29 April - Bridge closed for four weeks

Monday 27 May - The bridge re-opens under traffic control for six weeks

Monday 8 July - Bridge closing for three weeks

Monday 29 July - The bridge re-opens under traffic control for five weeks while finishing work is completed
The portable traffic signals are currently flashing yellow to remind motorists to exercise caution and reduce speed through the affected area.
